 Job Title: Engineering  Fellow (Artificial Intelligence /Machine Learning)
 Job Code:  AS20212207-66032 
 
Location: Plano, TX 
 
Position Summary: 
 
L3Harris Advanced Systems & Technologies (AS&T) division specializes in developing disruptive, next-generation technologies for advanced Unmanned Air Systems (UAS / UAV), advanced radar systems, next-generation weapon systems, and other RF sensor technologies using small company agility and big company experience. 
 
 We are searching for an Engineering  Fellow (Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning) Engineering  in our Advanced Systems & Technologies (AS&T) division, located in Plano,TX.
 Fellows demonstrate the multi-disciplinary expertise, theoretical knowledge, and ingenuity to establish industry-leading technical direction ensuring company and program success. AI/ML/SW Fellows additionally support sector/segment level leadership and business area growth through strategic technical roadmap development and innovation. 
 
 Major Job Activities: 
 Recognized as internal/external subject-matter-expert and thought leader with deep and substantive technical expertise in Software and the development of systems and products that implement AI/ML 
 Collaborate with internal teams and L3H partners to shape and deliver AI/ML solutions that meet customer needs 
 SW and AI/ML SME (Subject Matter Expert) during the iterative design phases of system solutions 
 Develops strategic technical vision and innovation roadmaps with corporate segment/sector/division leadership, program business areas driving business area growth 
 Lead proposal development with technical solutions/maturation, risk evaluation/mitigation, and costing 
 Demonstrated communication excellence with internal/external customers to share technical direction and influence new concepts, practices, and approachesResponsible for establishing the direction for new technical processes, systems, solutions, and products using significant conceptualization, reason, and interpretation considering both near and long-term implications 
 Develop dynamic vehicle aerodynamic, propulsion, and hardware/sensor models 
 Develop guidance algorithms to provide mission capability 
 Design and tune controllers for vehicle stability and control 
 Integrate a suite of sensor feedback for Navigation and Guidance algorithms development 
 Knowledge expert in leading flight software development and simulation in a variety of vehicle types 
 Leads root-cause failure investigation, identification, and resolution studies and communicates resulting issues, solution, and risk. 
 Other duties as assigned 
 
 Qualifications:
 Must be a U.S. citizen with existing secret DoD clearance with current 5 year update. Must be able to obtain and maintain additional clearances as required 
 BS in Engineering or Math required 
 MS or PhD in Engineering or Math preferred 
 A minimum of 20 years of demonstrated technical expertise in Software with a specialty in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning capabilities 
 A minimum of 20 years of demonstrated experience integrating and testing a variety of mission sensors (radar, optical, etc)
 Demonstrated technical Program Development leadership including planning and creation of development roadmaps, program execution, delegation of tasks, and verifying engineering rigor 
 Demonstrated problem solving and decision making/reasoning experience 
 Demonstrated business pursuit and capture experience with proposal/white paper support including technical and cost volume development 
 Demonstrated mentorship and career development support 
 Proficiency with algorithm and simulation model development tools including MATLAB/Simulink and C/C++ 
 Excellent communication skills (written, verbal, & presentation) including the ability to translate technical vision, direction, tasking, and status to multi-disciplinary teams and internal/external customers 
 Excellent people skills, with experience leading and collaborating in a multi-disciplinary, diverse, and dynamic team environment.
 Outstanding work ethic and commitment to organizational success 
 Proficient with Microsoft Office products 
 
 Preferred Skills: 
 
